<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 5000, 9000 Series Without Lowered heater Box - MAINTENANCE - HEATER WATER
        VALVE ADJUSTMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1601504" svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="1">
        <title>HEATER WATER VALVE ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <para>The water valve should be adjusted so that the valve is full on when the Blend-Air door is closed with
            about 25% compression of the door seal (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601512">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the passenger seat and cover from the top of the Blend-Air unit.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift water valve control link off the water valve control lever (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601512">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the valve control lever against the stop tab in the full ON position.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the control link adjuster until the link can be placed on the valve lever with the
                door closed and the seal compressed approximately 25%.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Adjust the HTR lever control cable (outlined below).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reinstall the Blend-Air unit cover and passenger seat.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1601512" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1601510B.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 12. Heater Core and Blend Door Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HEATER CORE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. DOOR ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>3. HEATER WATER VALVE</callout1>
                <callout1>4. WATER VALVE CONTROL LINK ADJUSTER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
